The ideal candidate is someone with a desire for continual learning and who possesses strong communication (oral and written), problem-solving, analytic, interpersonal skills, and is:
  -results-oriented 
  -detail-oriented 
  -accountable 
  -adaptable 
  -customer service oriented 
  -able to negotiate with and influence others 
  -able to work effectively (independently and/or within teams) across functional areas in a collaborative environment 
  -able to manage multiple tasks with competing timelines and deliverables 
  -able to receive and implement constructive feedback 
  -able to manage client's expectations by providing project production schedules  

Experience in the following is preferred:  
  -Proficiency in typography, branding, color theory, composition and other design principals to create modern graphic design products.   
  -Creating and effectively applying design techniques in a creative, cohesive, functional, and visually-pleasing manner to products such  
      as digital advertising, posters, brochures, environmental displays, logos and branding. 
  -Translating written/verbal themes and ideas into clear and impactful visual design products.  
  -Creating original artwork using image editing programs (ability to illustrate a plus). 
  -Proficiency in creative software including Adobe Creative Cloud (InDesign, Illustrator and Photoshop), and Power Point. 
  -Knowledge of accessibility standards a plus.